awtbuf/1.11/execution-metrics.json\\n./stats/org.latencyutils/LatencyUtils/2.0.3/execution-metrics.json\\n./stats/org.xmlunit/xmlunit-placeholders/2.10.2/execution-metrics.json\\n./stats/org.dom4j/dom4j/2.1.1/execution-metrics.json\\n./stats/commons-fileupload/commons-fileupload/1.6.0/execution-metrics.json\\n./stats/org.xmlunit/xmlunit-core/2.9.1/execution-metrics.json\\n./stats/aopalliance/aopalliance/1.0/execution-metrics.json\\n\",\"exit_code\":2,\"status\":\"failed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_3\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"The preserved failure data is under `human-intervention-logs`, not `logs`. I’m narrowing to the `netty-codec-stomp` artifacts now and checking whether the run reached generated tests, native-image compile, or failed later during native execution.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_4\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,260p' human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-codec-stomp:4.2.1.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_4\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,260p' human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-codec-stomp:4.2.1.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"{\\\"type\\\":\\\"thread.started\\\",\\\"thread_id\\\":\\\"019de941-9383-77c0-8248-8eb068037e2a\\\"}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"turn.started\\\"}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_0\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"agent_message\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Using `fix-missing-reachability-metadata` because the request is to repair library metadata for a specific coordinate. I’m reading that workflow first, then I’ll inspect the existing `io.netty:netty-codec-stomp:4.2.1.Final` entry and reproduce the failure.\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.started\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_1\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\"sed -n '1,220p' skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":null,\\\"status\\\":\\\"in_progress\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_1\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\"sed -n '1,220p' skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"---\\\\nname: fix-missing-reachability-metadata\\\\ndescription: Fix missing GraalVM reachability metadata for a specific library. Use when the user asks to fix or add metadata because required metadata is missing and tests or native-image runs fail with missing metadata errors.\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n# Fix missing reachability metadata entries in the reachability-metadata.json\\\\n\\\\n## Overview\\\\n\\\\nRun a reproduce-fix-verify loop for missing metadata errors. Keep running the target test until it passes with no new missing metadata entries.\\\\n\\\\nLibrary coordinates should be provided in the prompt in the format `group:artifact:version`. If you are not sure what the coordinates are, ask the user.\\\\n\\\\n## Workflow\\\\n\\\\n1. Reproduce the failure:\\\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` from repository root.\\\\n2. Capture the missing metadata from the error message:\\\\n   - Locate any `Missing*RegistrationError` (e.g. `MissingReflectionRegistrationError`, `MissingResourceRegistrationError`, or any other variant).\\\\n   - Copy the suggested JSON entry for the missing type into the corresponding section of the reachability-metadata.\\\\n3. Choose the target file and insert the entry:\\\\n   - Write to `metadata/<library-specific-metadata-directory>/reachability-metadata.json`.\\\\n   - Keep valid JSON and avoid duplicating an existing equivalent entry. If the type already exists but a method or field is missing, add only that method or field.\\\\n4. Add the missing `condition` field:\\\\n   - Infer it from the error stack trace.\\\\n   - Set the `condition` field to `{ \\\\\\\"typeReached\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"<class>\\\\\\\" }`, where `<class>` is the first class on the stack trace whose package shares the leading namespace with the tested library's package.\\\\n   - Package overlap can be partial, full package equality is not required.\\\\n   - Example: tested library's group `org.hibernate.orm...` and the class from a stack trace `org.hibernate.resource...` is a valid match.\\\\n\\\\n5. Verify and iterate:\\\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` again.\\\\n   - If another missing entry appears, repeat from step 2.\\\\n   - Finish only when the test run succeeds.\\\\n\\\\n## Error Patterns\\\\n\\\\nUse this reference when deriving the missing entry and condition.\\\\n\\\\n### Missing Registration Entry Pattern\\\\n\\\\nExample error shape:\\\\n\\\\n```text\\\\nCaused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError:\\\\nCannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator()'\\\\n...\\\\nadd the following to the 'reflection' section of reachability-metadata.json:\\\\n{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"methods\\\\\\\": [{ \\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"<init>\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"parameterTypes\\\\\\\": [] }]\\\\n}\\\\n...\\\\nat org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder.instantiateGeneratorViaDefaultConstructor(...)\\\\nat org.hibernate.resource.beans.internal.Helper$2.produceBeanInstance(...)\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n### Condition Inference\\\\n\\\\nFor missing type `org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator`, a valid condition class is:\\\\n\\\\n`org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder`\\\\n\\\\nReason: both share the leading namespace `org.hibernate`, which is sufficient for this workflow.\\\\n\\\\n## Environment Troubleshooting\\\\n\\\\n- If failures look unrelated or tooling looks inconsistent, verify both `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME` point to a compatible GraalVM JDK distribution.\\\\n- If they are not set to GraalVM, ask the user to provide the correct GraalVM distribution path and retry.\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.started\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_2\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\"rg --files | rg 'netty-codec-stomp|stomp'\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":null,\\\"status\\\":\\\"in_progress\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_2\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\"rg --files | rg 'netty-codec-stomp|stomp'\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"metadata/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.1.74.Final/reachability-metadata.json\\\\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/index.json\\\\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.2.1.Final/reachability-metadata.json\\\\ntests/src/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.1.74.Final/build.gradle\\\\ntests/src/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.1.74.Final/settings.gradle\\\\ntests/src/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.1.74.Final/src/test/java/io_netty/netty_codec_stomp/Netty_codec_stompTest.java\\\\ntests/src/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.1.74.Final/gradle.properties\\\\ntests/src/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.1.74.Final/user-code-filter.json\\\\ntests/src/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.1.74.Final/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-vintage.xml\\\\ntests/src/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.1.74.Final/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml\\\\nstats/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.1.74.Final/stats.json\\\\nstats/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/4.1.74.Final/execution-metrics.json\\\\n\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.started\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_3\\\",\\\"type\\\"